---
import federalData from '../../data/federal-funds.json';
---

<div class="rounded-lg border border-wtp-red/30 bg-wtp-red/5 p-6 md:p-8">
  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
    <span class="mt-0.5 text-2xl leading-none">⚠</span>
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-wtp-red">Cliff scenarios</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-wtp-cream/70">
        What happens to PA's structural deficit if any of these federal cuts materialize:
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <dl class="mt-6 space-y-5">
    {federalData.riskScenarios.map((scenario) => (
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-l-2 border-wtp-red/40 pl-4">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <dt class="font-semibold text-white">{scenario.label}</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-wtp-cream/70">{scenario.shortDescription}</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-right">
          <div class="font-mono text-2xl font-bold text-wtp-red md:text-3xl">
            +${(scenario.deficitImpactUSD / 1e9).toFixed(1)}B
          </div>
          <div class="text-xs text-wtp-cream/40">added to deficit</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </dl>

  <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-wtp-cream/40">
    Sources: KFF Medicaid State Indicators, CMS FMAP tables, PA Office of the Budget federal funds reporting. Scenario impacts are estimates based on current program sizes; actual cuts would depend on specific federal legislation.
  </p>
</div>
